.TH "mod_timer_pending" 9 "mod_timer_pending" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mod_timer_pending \- modify a pending timer's timeout
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" mod_timer_pending
.BI "(struct timer_list *timer "  ","
.BI "unsigned long expires "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "timer" 12
the pending timer to be modified
.IP "expires" 12
new timeout in jiffies
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBmod_timer_pending\fP is the same for pending timers as \fBmod_timer\fP,
but will not re-activate and modify already deleted timers.

It is useful for unserialized use of timers.
